    "body": "### Problem\n\nPmenu with `pumborder=none` results in extra cells (to its right and bottom) that will not draw floating window if it is opened some time after pmenu.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create 'init-pumborder-none.lua' with the following content:\n\n    ```lua\n    vim.o.pumborder = 'none'\n\n    -- Prepare buffer for easier repro\n    vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, false, { 'aa ab', '' })\n    vim.api.nvim_win_set_cursor(0, { 2, 0 })\n\n    -- Define mapping that shows pmenu and *then* opens float\n    local show_pum_and_float = function()\n      vim.api.nvim_input('<C-n>')\n\n      local config = { relative = 'editor', row = 1, col = 10, height = 10, width = 10, border = 'single' }\n      local buf_id = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\n      vim.defer_fn(function() vim.api.nvim_open_win(buf_id, false, config) end, 100)\n    end\n    vim.keymap.set('i', '<M-m>', show_pum_and_float)\n    ```\n2. `nvim --clean -u init-pumborder-none.lua`.\n3. Start Insert mode and press `<M-m>`. After 100 ms a floating window appears and some of its part (two column cells to the right of pmenu) is not drawn. Here is how it looks:\n\n<img width=\"2880\" height=\"1734\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/58e5c1eb-698d-4052-8d99-43954db7c420\" />\n\nEverything works as expected if:\n- Value of 'pumborder' is not 'none'.\n- Floating window is opened not with `defer_fn`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFloating window can always be rendered in full.\n\nCc @glepnir \n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1467+g671841673e\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nProbably not, as it doesn't have everything necessary to reproduce this\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64, 6.17.3-arch2-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.2.2-arch1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nAppimage",
